Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance evaluation of caching systems in the context of evolving Internet transfer modes. This topic falls under the broad category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a new model for analyzing the performance of cascade of caches, which involves statistical analysis and modeling of traffic patterns. This could be relevant to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY), architecture (cs.AR), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
